random noise, indicate that for $H \\leq 1$,\nsupercritical exponential growth leads to saturation, but not turbulence. For\nhigher $3 \\leq H \\leq 10$, a turbulent transition occurs, and is maintained at\n$H=10$. For $H \\geq 30$, the turbulent transition still occurs, but is short\nlived, as the turbulent state quickly collapses. In addition, for $H \\geq 3$,\nan inertial subrange is identified, with the perturbation energy exhibiting a\n$-5/3$ power law dependence on wave number.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Dec 2020 05:39:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-24"}
